				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think it's even harder to collaborate with hardware than it is with software. There are so few limitations that preferences come out immediately. Not only does everyone have stylistic differences but will implement at different levels of abstraction, will write more or less synthesizable code and have a different thoughts on accuracy. With hardware often these differences aren't compatible. Really it will come down to whoever starts the HDL module or a lot of foundation logic will be overwritten by each contributor to suit their needs.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

